<div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Funny idea, but it sounds physically impossible - mostly because of the huge size of 2 DIP-40 ICs.  If you have some creative way of mounting those chips, maybe.  I would think that multiple 2-layer boards stacked would do better than a 4-layer+ board.  Those big DIP parts will severely restrict part placement and routing.<br /></div><br /><br />Yeah I was even considering two stacked 4 layer boards if need be.  The CPU and PPU will easily fit length or width wise but they aren't the only thing in there obviously.  The gameboy has over 5x3" and they are 2" each.  <br /><br />I wouldn't have really thought it was possible till I sized the mobo and the gameboy internals next to each other.  One of the biggest things I'm concerned about is improper placement/routing causing interference.  Wasn't there an issue with that on some version of the NES/FC?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4832">infiniteneslives</a> — Sat Sep 03, 2011 2:58 am</p><hr />
