<div class="quotetitle">infiniteneslives wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />For the CIC onboard, is it needed to prevent resets?  Could I just toss it entirely or would have have to have it installed with pin 4 clipped?<br /></div><br />You can leave out the CIC.<br /><br />The CIC patent mentions cartridges that don't enable the ROMs until the key detects a valid lock. This feature was used by Super NES games using some of the coprocessors and by a limited-edition "Nintendo World Championships" NES game. But because it wasn't used on any retail NES games, Nintendo left it out of the redesigned NES.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Sep 01, 2011 7:41 am</p><hr />
